verbose_text: Cholesterol derived from LDL is modified and binds to scavenger receptor SR-B1 in tissues, particularly the vasculature, activating macrophage ATP binding cassette, subfamily A (ABCA1) and ABCG1 receptors, leading macrophage cholesterol to be taken up by lipid-poor apolipoprotein A1 after binding with the ABCA1 transporter.
